{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W3PDsvUpqFQX4GRxVTzLAs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me compose the complete audit findings and create the ConfigMap.\n\nKey findings to include:\n\n**CRITICAL**:\n1. xpack.security.enabled = false — full security disabled, no authentication or authorization\n2. xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled = false — HTTP API on port 9200 is plaintext\n3. xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled = false — inter-node transport is plaintext\n4. No NetworkPolicy — cluster-wide access to ports 9200 and 9300 unrestricted\n5. xpack.security.audit.enabled = false — no security audit logging\n6. No pod security context — containers run without securityContext (no runAsNonRoot, no readOnlyRootFilesystem, no allowPrivilegeEscalation=false)\n\n**HIGH**:\n7. audit-index has no ILM policy — data retention uncontrolled\n8. All nodes are master + data + ingest — no role separation, increases blast radius\n9. updateStrategy: OnDelete — security patches not applied automatically on template update\n10. xpack.watcher.encrypt_sensitive_data = false — Watcher secrets stored unencrypted\n11. No Kubernetes Secrets in namespace — no TLS certificates provisioned\n\n**MEDIUM**:\n12. Elasticsearch 8.11.1 (released Nov 2023) — may be behind on CVE patches\n13. network.host: 0.0.0.0 — listens on all interfaces on each pod\n14. audit-index shard allocation routing: routing.allocation.require.tier=hot — non-default but intentional\n15. action.destructive_requires_name = true — POSITIVE\n16. http.cors.enabled = false — POSITIVE\n17. xpack.security.fips_mode.enabled = false\n18. xpack.monitoring.collection.enabled = false — no internal metrics\n19. xpack.license.self_generated.type = basic — basic license, but in Elasticsearch 8.x, security features like authentication and TLS are available even with the basic license\n\n; the explicit `xpack.security.enabled: false` in the config is what's actually disabling them\n\nNow I'm ready to write up the findings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1760,"cache_read_input_tokens":43226,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1760},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4358e053-ad1e-458e-af73-bbbda8fa8007","uuid":"ca3ae0b9-6090-4c6f-97ec-baec20c79ee4","request_id":"req_011CcLEs5jCmYnH8m1LTugkR"}
