{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W3PDsvUpqFQX4GRxVTzLAs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017jcfmLhoUyGs7X8ouBYAxz","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\nELASTICSEARCH SECURITY & COMPLIANCE AUDIT\n==========================================\nDate: 2026-06-23\nCluster: es-cluster (UUID: _UHHqzGOTW2tiwfKgQblNQ)\nVersion: 8.11.1 (Lucene 9.8.0, JDK 21.0.1)\nNodes: 3 (es-cluster-0 [master*], es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2)\nLicense: basic (self-generated)\nAuditor: read-only inspection — no cluster changes made\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSEVERITY SUMMARY\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nCRITICAL : 4 findings\nHIGH     : 3 findings\nMEDIUM   : 4 findings\nLOW/INFO : 5 findings\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nCRITICAL FINDINGS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n[C1] X-Pack Security Entirely Disabled\n  Setting: xpack.security.enabled = false  (elasticsearch.yml, applied to all 3 nodes)\n  Impact:  No authentication or authorization is enforced. Any client that can\n           reach port 9200 (HTTP) or 9300 (transport) can read, write, delete,\n           or reconfigure the cluster without credentials. In ES 8.x the security\n           subsystem is enabled by default; this is an explicit override.\n  Evidence: curl http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/ returns cluster info\n           without any credentials. All API endpoints are fully open.\n\n[C2] HTTP Transport Unencrypted (TLS Disabled)\n  Setting: xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled = false\n           xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled = false\n  Impact:  All client-to-node traffic (port 9200) and all inter-node traffic\n           (port 9300) are transmitted in plaintext. Credentials, queries, and\n           data (including documents in audit-index) are visible to any observer\n           on the pod network. No TLS certificates have been provisioned\n           (zero Secrets exist in the namespace).\n  Evidence: No Secrets found in namespace; node settings confirm ssl.enabled=false\n           on both http and transport layers across all three nodes.\n\n[C3] No Kubernetes NetworkPolicy — Unrestricted Cluster-Wide Access\n  Setting: No NetworkPolicy objects exist in the elasticsearch namespace.\n  Impact:  Any pod in any namespace on the cluster can reach port 9200 (HTTP\n           API) and port 9300 (transport) on every Elasticsearch node without\n           restriction. Combined with C1 (no authentication), this means the\n           cluster data and administrative API are exposed to all workloads.\n  Evidence: kubectl -n elasticsearch get networkpolicy returns empty list.\n           Services: es-http (ClusterIP 10.96.254.238:9200), es-cluster\n           (headless :9300); network.host=0.0.0.0 on all nodes.\n\n[C4] Security Audit Logging Disabled\n  Setting: xpack.security.audit.enabled = false\n  Impact:  No record is kept of authentication attempts, access grants/denials,\n           privilege escalations, or configuration changes. Given that security\n           (C1) is disabled, all access is anonymous and completely invisible to\n           audit. There is no forensic trail if the cluster has been accessed\n           inappropriately.\n  Evidence: Default setting confirmed from cluster defaults API.\n           (Relevant events that WOULD be captured if enabled:\n           ACCESS_DENIED, ACCESS_GRANTED, AUTHENTICATION_FAILED,\n           ANONYMOUS_ACCESS_DENIED, CONNECTION_DENIED, SECURITY_CONFIG_CHANGE)\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nHIGH FINDINGS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n[H1] No Pod-Level Security Context — Containers May Run as Root\n  Setting: spec.securityContext: {} and container securityContext: {}\n           (StatefulSet es-cluster, all 3 pods)\n  Impact:  No runAsNonRoot, no allowPrivilegeEscalation=false, no\n           readOnlyRootFilesystem, no seccompProfile. The Elasticsearch process\n           runs as whatever user the image defaults to, with no privilege\n           boundary enforced by Kubernetes. A container escape would have\n           elevated host access.\n  Evidence: kubectl get pod es-cluster-0 -o jsonpath='{.spec.securityContext}'\n           returns '{}'; container securityContext also '{}' on all nodes.\n\n[H2] audit-index Has No ILM (Index Lifecycle Management) Policy\n  Setting: _ilm/explain for audit-index returns \"managed\": false\n  Impact:  An index named \"audit-index\" stores compliance-sensitive data with\n           no retention policy. Data is never rolled over, aged, or deleted on\n           schedule. Over time this leads to unconstrained disk growth, and\n           there is no guarantee that audit data is retained for a required\n           minimum period or purged after a required maximum period.\n  Evidence: GET audit-index/_ilm/explain => {\"managed\":false}\n           Fourteen ILM policies exist (system/built-in) but none is\n           attached to audit-index.\n\n[H3] Watcher Sensitive Data Stored Unencrypted\n  Setting: xpack.watcher.encrypt_sensitive_data = false\n  Impact:  Any secrets stored in Watcher actions (e.g., webhook URLs, SMTP\n           credentials, Slack tokens) are stored in plaintext in the .watches\n           index. Since security is disabled (C1) and audit logging is off (C4),\n           these secrets are readable by any unauthenticated caller.\n  Evidence: Default setting confirmed from cluster defaults API.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nMEDIUM FINDINGS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n[M1] All Nodes Are Master + Data + Ingest — No Role Separation\n  Setting: node.roles: [master, data, ingest] on all 3 nodes\n  Impact:  All three nodes are master-eligible, meaning any node could become\n           cluster master. A compromised or overloaded data node can disrupt\n           elections. Best practice for production is dedicated master nodes\n           (3 voting-only masters) separate from data and ingest nodes.\n  Evidence: _cat/nodes?h=role shows 'dim' for all three nodes.\n           Node settings confirm roles=[master,data,ingest] on each.\n\n[M2] StatefulSet updateStrategy: OnDelete — Security Patches Not Auto-Applied\n  Setting: spec.updateStrategy.type: OnDelete\n  Impact:  When the StatefulSet pod template is updated (e.g., for a CVE patch\n           or config change), existing pods are NOT restarted automatically.\n           Pods must be manually deleted to pick up changes. This creates a\n           window where running nodes diverge from the declared configuration\n           indefinitely.\n  Evidence: StatefulSet manifest shows updateStrategy.type=OnDelete.\n\n[M3] Internal Monitoring Disabled — No Visibility Into Cluster Health Metrics\n  Setting: xpack.monitoring.collection.enabled = false\n  Impact:  Node-level metrics (JVM heap, GC, disk I/O, indexing latency) are\n           not collected or stored. Observed at audit time: CPU throttling is\n           actively occurring (472 throttle events in 1081 CFS periods on\n           es-cluster-2 alone, ~44% throttle rate), heap at 59% on es-cluster-1.\n           Without monitoring these signals are invisible to operators.\n  Evidence: Defaults API confirms monitoring disabled; node stats show cgroup\n           cpu throttling on all nodes.\n\n[M4] Version 8.11.1 — Released November 2023, Potentially Behind on CVE Patches\n  Setting: version.number = 8.11.1, build_date = 2023-11-11\n  Impact:  The Elasticsearch 8.x line has received subsequent releases. Running\n           a version from November 2023 means known vulnerabilities fixed in\n           later patch releases may be present. Should be evaluated against\n           Elastic security advisories and upgraded to the latest 8.x patch.\n  Evidence: GET / returns version.number=8.11.1, build_date=2023-11-11.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nLOW / INFORMATIONAL\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n[L1] Non-Default Index Routing on audit-index (Intentional, Verify)\n  Settings applied (from _all/_settings):\n    index.routing.allocation.require.tier = hot\n    index.routing.allocation.include._tier_preference = data_content\n  These are non-default settings that constrain shard placement to nodes\n  with attribute tier=hot (all 3 nodes carry node.attr.tier=hot in config).\n  This appears intentional but should be confirmed as policy.\n\n[L2] Persistent and Transient Cluster Settings Are Empty\n  GET /_cluster/settings?flat_settings=true returns:\n    {\"persistent\":{},\"transient\":{}}\n  No hardening overrides (e.g., forced TLS, disable dynamic scripting,\n  restrict snapshot repos) have been applied at the cluster settings level.\n  All behavior is driven by elasticsearch.yml and defaults.\n\n[L3] Positive Control: action.destructive_requires_name = true\n  This default is active and confirmed. DELETE /_all or DELETE /index-*\n  wildcard-style destructive operations are blocked, reducing accidental\n  data loss risk.\n\n[L4] CORS Disabled — Positive Control\n  http.cors.enabled = false (default, confirmed).\n  Cross-origin browser requests to the HTTP API are rejected.\n\n[L5] Elasticsearch Enrollment and FIPS Mode Both Disabled\n  xpack.security.enrollment.enabled = false — auto-enrollment of new nodes\n  disabled (acceptable for a static 3-node cluster).\n  xpack.security.fips_mode.enabled = false — cluster is not running in\n  FIPS 140-2 mode. If regulatory compliance requires FIPS, this must be\n  addressed at cluster build time (requires a FIPS JVM and keystore changes).\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nRECOMMENDED REMEDIATION PRIORITY\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n1. [C1+C2] Enable xpack.security.enabled=true and configure TLS certificates\n   for both HTTP and transport layers before any network exposure.\n2. [C3] Apply a NetworkPolicy to restrict ingress to port 9200 and 9300\n   to only authorized source namespaces/pods.\n3. [C4] Enable xpack.security.audit.enabled=true to begin capturing an\n   access trail.\n4. [H1] Add a pod securityContext (runAsNonRoot=true, allowPrivilegeEscalation\n   =false, seccompProfile=RuntimeDefault) to the StatefulSet template.\n5. [H2] Attach an ILM policy to audit-index with defined retention bounds.\n6. [H3] Set xpack.watcher.encrypt_sensitive_data=true (requires keystore setup).\n7. [M1-M4] Address role separation, update strategy, monitoring, and version\n   patching as operational hardening steps.\n\nNOTE: This audit was performed read-only. No cluster settings, indices,\nsecrets, or Kubernetes resources were modified during this audit.\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with security findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1760,"cache_read_input_tokens":43226,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1760},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4358e053-ad1e-458e-af73-bbbda8fa8007","uuid":"2b4442f7-f9c0-43e6-980c-222298d4540b","request_id":"req_011CcLEs5jCmYnH8m1LTugkR"}
